''This is a VBA Macro code snippet used to clear content within the specified range, cell, or table.
''Example: In this snippet, I will clear a range from B8 to K1000 and the same time, the cell Q3 and S3.
''Created by: Gerald John Alviar https://ph.linkedin.com/in/geraldalviar, please contact me if you use it. This will help to improve my snippet.


Sub ClearWorkSheetData()
Range("B8:K1000").ClearContents 'Clearcontent command, you can specify what to clear
Range("Q3,S3").ClearContents
End Sub

'Other Methods for Clear
'   .Clear 'Clears Everything   
'   .ClearComments 'Clear Comments  
'   .ClearFormats 'Clears Formatting   
'   .ClearHyperlinks 'Clear Hyperlinks  
'   .ClearNotes 'Clear Notes
'   .ClearOutline 'Clears Outline
